Roles?
it is the collections of permissions.
which are used to define what actions a user can perform and what resources a user can access in Liferay.

types of roles?
there is five types of roles in liferay
1)Regular Role -A globally scoped role whose permissions apply throughout the entire Liferay instance. 
2)site Role- A role with permissions limited to a specific site. 
3)Organizatiom Role-A role with permissions limited to a specific organization. 
4)Asset Library Role-A role scoped to an asset library (permissions apply only within that library).
5)Account Role-An Account Role defines what actions a user can perform within a specific Account
